<section class="container py-12 md:py-16">
  <div class="grid gap-16 md:grid-cols-2 md:items-center">
    <!-- Image -->
    <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-stone-100">
      <img
        src="/images/founder.jpg"
        alt="Pam Sweeney, founder of Purest Electrolyte, on the beach"
        class="w-full h-auto object-contain"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Text -->
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">Founder</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
        I made it for myself first. Then everything changed.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-foreground/80">
        <p>
          I ended up in the hospital with hyponatremia. For years I couldn't
          understand what had really happened to me. Or why I kept feeling
          depleted no matter what I did. I tried every electrolyte on the market.
          Nothing worked. Nothing was clean. Nothing was real.
        </p>
        <p>
          We live at 9,000 feet in Aspen, Colorado. I have four kids, all
          high-level athletes. The altitude, the exertion, the sweat — we needed
          something that actually worked. So I stopped looking for it and started
          making it. Real freeze-dried fruit. French gray sea salt. Nothing else.
        </p>
        <p>
          Once I understood what an electrolyte actually needed to have in it,
          my life changed. And so did the lives of my children.
        </p>
      </div>
      <p class="font-serif text-lg italic text-foreground/60">— Pam Sweeney, Founder</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
